      "comment": "ALTA WILLIAM (6) has been racing against stronger opposition at Menangle where he did some work last start but stuck on to be beaten 4.6 metres. He'll enjoy the return to a venue where he has won both attempts, coming from the back row to score by close to 10m in his latest visit three back. CASSIUS DECK (8) has been excellent of late and made it two wins in a row when successful at his latest appearance at this circuit and distance, coming from a similar barrier and getting home by 2 metres. With even luck he could land the hat trick. SMOOTH BUZZ (7) has ground to make up on CASSIUS DECK after finishing fifth to him last start but he draws inside that rival tonight and that could make a difference. BAXTER RED (5) draws lower than when fifth after working last start and had placed in his previous two outings here.",
